content:
Drive self-serve case deflection in your Service Catalog site with Einstein Copilot.

Einstein Copilot is your AI assistant for Service Catalog. Through a conversational interface, Copilot uses an LLM to identify and execute relevant actions to resolve customer contact reasons without customers navigating your catalog or contacting support.

Copilot actions are specific tasks that Copilot completes. In Service Catalog, if a customer asks for help updating their phone number or email, Copilot initiates an action for each service and either opens a catalog item request for the customer or provides them a link to the catalog item in your site.

To integrate Copilot in Service Catalog, you must have the required Service Catalog and Einstein Copilot permissions and licensing. You also need to build a Service Catalog that contains at least one active catalog category, catalog item, and catalog fulfillment.

To get started with Copilot, review the following:

* Familiarize yourself with Service Catalog actions, Copilot output types, and their relation to catalog items.
* Setup Copilot in Service Catalog by accessing the Sample Catalog Items (Beta), Set Up Standard Service Catalog Actions (Beta), and Set Up Custom Service Catalog Actions (Beta).

Note: This feature is a Beta Service. Customer may opt to try such Beta Service in its sole discretion. Any use of the Beta Service is subject to the applicable Beta Services Terms provided at Agreements and Terms.
title: Integrating AI into Your Service Catalog with Einstein Copilot
